      <title>A Call to Chapel with Dr. Cornel West (In-Person and Virtually) at Cramton Auditorium</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52426001021329/huge/62b79f97af963b8bfa5630bc0c146d26367284b2.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Sun, 12 Apr 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>Dr. Cornel West, affectionately known to many as Brother West, is the Dietrich Bonhoeffer Chair at Union Theological Seminary. Dr. West teaches on the works of Dietrich Bonhoeffer, as well as courses in Philosophy of Religion, African American Critical Thought, and a wide range of subjects -- including but by no means limited to, the classics, philosophy, politics, cultural theory, literature, and music. He has a passion to communicate to a vast variety of publics in order to keep alive the legacy of Martin Luther King, Jr. – a legacy of telling the truth and bearing witness to love and justice.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>To learn about our guest speaker, click here.</p>

