    <item>
      <title>Pepsi Talk Series Hosted by NFL Legend Santana Moss at Cook Hall (George W. Cook Hall)</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52577264632454/huge/90f2dbc1f1c2010342964d73ede24f35ebf49cbe.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Mon, 13 Apr 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>🚨 Special Guest Alert 🚨</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Join this Monday to hear Santana Moss, Washington Commanders’ legend, speak about his experience and so much more! Hosted by his nephew, Sinorice Moss, a current Howard University football player.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>A first-round pick by the New York Jets, Moss went on to make his mark in Washington, where he spent 10 seasons delivering some of the most productive years of his career. In his debut season there, he earned Pro Bowl honors and Second-Team All-Pro, recording 84 receptions for a career-high 1,483 yards and 9 touchdowns — setting a franchise record.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>He finished his Washington career ranked:
<br>🏈 3rd in receptions (581)
<br>🏈 4th in receiving yards (7,867)
<br>🏈 7th in receiving touchdowns (47)</p>

<p> </p>

<p>In 2025, he was honored with induction into the Washington Commanders Ring of Fame. Don’t miss this powerful conversation on legacy, leadership, and life beyond the game.</p>

<p>#HowardUniversity #BisonPride #NFL #SantanaMoss #StudentAthletes #Legacy #HUBison</p>

