      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52461467218735/huge/15e548bf4bd384612c53360b7a1c150676528335.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Mon, 13 Apr 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>The 2026 CADSA Symposium on How Data and AI Are Reshaping Research will explore how emerging technologies are transforming the research enterprise, from accelerating discovery, enabling interdisciplinary collaboration, and driving inclusive innovation. Hosted by Howard University’s Center for Applied Data Science and Analytics (CADSA), the symposium brings together students, faculty, and research partners for a day of flash talks, think tanks, panels, and poster sessions that highlight how data and AI are unlocking insights, informing solutions to pressing societal challenges, and advancing national goals to expand opportunity and improve lives.</p>

