    <item>
      <title>A Night With the Aksumites: Howard EESA’s Fourth Annual Benefit Dinner at Blackburn Center (Armour J. Blackburn University Center)</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52550397092216/huge/8709df75fc1dc824e3f44cd7f0bb2d7c7ffdde2a.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Mon, 13 Apr 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>The Howard University Ethiopian and Eritrean Student Association, in collaboration with the Howard Ethiopian and Eritrean Alumni Association, will host its fourth annual benefit dinner, A Night With the Aksumites, on April 13. The event celebrates the shared cultural heritage of Ethiopia and Eritrea, drawing inspiration from the ancient Aksumite Empire, a historic center of civilization, trade and culture in East Africa.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>The evening will feature a curated dining experience, live Ethiopian jazz, a fashion show by The GENESIS Models, and traditional dance performances by the Kibret Dance Team. Additional programming includes a silent auction, raffle giveaways and the announcement of scholarship recipients. Organizers will also announce the winners of the Saron S. Bekabil Memorial Scholarship, which supports Ethiopian and Eritrean students at Howard University.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>All proceeds will benefit Beloved Mission, a nonprofit organization that provides essential care for pediatric oncology patients in Ethiopia, Eritrea and other underserved communities worldwide. Attire for the event is cultural or formal.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>For more information, visit belovedmission.org. To support the scholarship fund, visit:
<br><a href="https://www.givecampus.com/schools/HowardUniversity/saron-s-bekabil-memorial-scholarship-campaign/?a=12666173">https://www.givecampus.com/schools/HowardUniversity/saron-s-bekabil-memorial-scholarship-campaign/?a=12666173</a></p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/a-night-with-the-aksumites-howard-eesas-fourth-annual-benefit-dinner">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A A Night With the Aksumites%3A Howard EESA%E2%80%99s Fourth Annual Benefit Dinner&amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Apr 13%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AThe Howard University Ethiopian and Eritrean Student Association%2C in collaboration with the Howard Ethiopian and Eritrean Alumni Association%2C will host its fourth annual benefit dinner%2C A Night With the Aksumites%2C on April 13. The event celebrates the shared cultural heritage of Ethiopia and Eritrea%2C drawing inspiration from the ancient Aksumite Empire%2C a historic center of civilization%2C trade and culture in East Africa.%0A%0A %0A%0AThe evening will feature a curated dining experience%2C live Ethiopian jazz%2C a fashion show by The GENESIS Models%2C and traditional dance performances by the Kibret Dance Team. Additional programming includes a silent auction%2C raffle giveaways and the announcement of scholarship recipients. Organizers will also announce the winners of the Saron S. Bekabil Memorial Scholarship%2C which supports Ethiopian and Eritrean students at Howard University.%0A%0A %0A%0AAll proceeds will benefit Beloved Mission%2C a nonprofit organization that provides essential care for pediatric oncology patients in Ethiopia%2C Eritrea and other underserved communities worldwide. Attire for the event is cultural or formal.%0A%0A %0A%0AFor more information%2C visit belovedmission.org. To support the scholarship fund%2C visit%3A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.givecampus.com%2Fschools%2FHowardUniversity%2Fsaron-s-bekabil-memorial-scholarship-campaign%2F%3Fa%3D12666173%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2Fa-night-with-the-aksumites-howard-eesas-fourth-annual-benefit-dinner%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
